snippet.textDisplay: the artwork is the same car but in different positions in time, the fans want the same thing from the distant past, now still in the present. Time progresses but nothing changes. The artwork could also be speaking to the glorification of the past, it looks nice in the distance but get a closer view and you realise the present is just the same. And further, after the first, very close car. We have The Strokes text in big letters, acting like a barrier in a sense. Maybe trying to say, don’t look beyond what’s right in front of you (the new album). This is The Strokes and we’re proud of it. This could all be wrong of course, just some thoughts I had.
